<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-486-290  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 486 290.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  May 21 1990 v7 n21 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>US West unveils new 'self-healing' services. (RBHC to invest $35million for services insulating networks from outages) (regionalBell holding company)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>US West Communications Inc introduces two fiber-optics-basedself-healing services that will automatically restorecommunication within milliseconds of a disruption.andP;  TheSelf-Healing Alternate Route Protection (SHARP) service isdesigned to give T1 and T3 users alternate paths into the localexchange network.andP;  It will cost $696 a month for T1 users and$4,042 a month for T3 users.andP;  The Self-Healing Network Services(SHNS) is a T3 offering that offers fail-safe, high-capacityvoice, data and video links between multiple sites within a localgeographic region.andP;  SHNS will link customer sites and US Westcentral office switches in a serial fashion with tow concentric,counter-rotating 45M-bit per second T3 fiber-optic rings.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   U S West Inc. (services).andO;Ticker:    USW.andO;Topic:     Telephone CompaniesFiber OpticsT3 CommunicationsT1 CommunicationsSelf-Repair CapabilityPower FailureUser AidsTelephone Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>